				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">za909 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Two things that stood out to me:<br />- $2007 is the PPU_DATA register, your table makes it look like it is part of the mirorred address space.<br /></div><br />The same is true of &quot;Sound &amp; Joypad Ports&quot; - the &quot;unused&quot; section following it should begin at $4018, not $4017.<br /><br />Also, most of the &quot;unused&quot; areas aren't really unused - they're <em>mirrors</em> of the regions preceding them. The only exception is $4018-$5FFF, which really <strong>is</strong> unused (and is used by some cartridges for ROM/RAM or I/O registers).<br /><br />Also also, $0200-$02FF isn't formally defined as Sprite Data - most games just happen to use it that way because it's adjacent to the Stack, an area which <em>does</em> have a special meaning (and which typically won't be used for general-purpose variables).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
